      "message": "my idea was to simply handle the null pointer exception here.\nThe handling you did will not get the nullpointer exception.\nThis method can still return null, and then you will have a nullpointer at line 302, for example.\n\nWhat I suggest is to check for the null here:\n\nUserBusinessLogicExt userBusinessLogic = (UserBusinessLogicExt) ctx.getBean(\"userBusinessLogicExt\");\nif (userBusinessLogic == null) {\n    //add the logs you want and then throw the exception\n    throw new PortalAPIException([...]\n}\n\nreturn userBusinessLogic;",
